
sudo mv /usr/local/bin/node /usr/local/bin/node_old
sudo mv /usr/local/bin/npm /usr/local/bin/npm_old

if you get:
jenkinsadmin@Jenkins-BuildServer:/var/lib/jenkins$ node -v
-bash: /usr/local/bin/node: No such file or directory

but if you run and get :
jenkinsadmin@Jenkins-BuildServer:/var/lib/jenkins$ /usr/bin/node -v
v22.22.0


then do this:
jenkinsadmin@Jenkins-BuildServer:/var/lib/jenkins$ node -v
-bash: /usr/local/bin/node: No such file or directory
jenkinsadmin@Jenkins-BuildServer:/var/lib/jenkins$ export PATH=/usr/bin:$PATH
jenkinsadmin@Jenkins-BuildServer:/var/lib/jenkins$ source ~/.bashrc
node -v
v22.22.0
jenkinsadmin@Jenkins-BuildServer:/var/lib/jenkins$ which node
/usr/bin/node
jenkinsadmin@Jenkins-BuildServer:/var/lib/jenkins$












curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.39.7/install.sh | bash
source ~/.bashrc


verify:nvm --version

Install a specific Node version: 
nvm install 24.11.0


Use that version
nvm use 24.11.0


Check:
node -v
npm -v


(Optional) Set default Node version:
nvm alias default 24.11.0


### Hold Node.js package (recommended)
1️⃣ Check Node package name
dpkg -l | grep nodejs

Usually it’s: nodejs


Put Node.js on hold (PREVENT upgrades)
sudo apt-mark hold nodejs

Verify hold status
apt-mark showhold


Expected output: nodejs
